quest_title: If A and B are two sets, then \(A \times B = B \times A\) iff
explanation_txt:
For the two cartesian products, \(A \times B\) and \(B \times A\) to be equal, the sets must themselves be equal. This is because for every element \( \ (a,b) \ \) in \(A \times B\), there is an equivalent element, \( \ (b,a) \ \) in \(B \times A\). And, \( \ (a,b) \ = \ (b,a) \ \) means, \(a = b\). This is equivalent to saying \(A = B\).

Also, two sets \(A\) and \(B\) are equal only iff they are subsets of each other.

For furhter clarity, consider two singleton sets, \(A = \{a\} \) and \(B = \{b\}\). Then, \(A \times B = \{(a,b)\}\) and \(B \times A = \{(b,a)\}\).

\(A \times B =B \times A\) means, \( \ (a,b) \ = \ (b,a) \ \)

So, \(a=b\)

And finally, \(A = B\).

quest_title: The position vectors of the points A, B, C are \((2i+j-k),\) \((3i-2j+k)\) and \((i+4j-3k)\) respectively. These points
explanation_txt:
\(\overrightarrow{AB} =(3-2)i+(-2-1)j+(1+1)k=i-3j+2k\)

\(\overrightarrow{BC} =(1-3)i+(4+2)j+(-3-1)k=-2i+6j-4k\)

\(\overrightarrow{CA} =(2-1)i+(1-4)j+(-1+3)k=i-3j-2k\)

\(|\overrightarrow{AB} |\, =\sqrt{1+9+4} =\sqrt{14} \)

\(|\overrightarrow{BC} |\, =\sqrt{4+36+16} =\sqrt{56} =2\sqrt{14} \)

\(|\overrightarrow{CA} |\, =\sqrt{1+9+4} =\sqrt{14} \)

So, \(|\overrightarrow{AB} |+|\overrightarrow{AC} |=\, |\, \overrightarrow{BC} \, |\) and angle between AB and BC is 180\(\mathrm{{}^\circ}\).

Hence A, B, C are collinear.

quest_title: A person measures the time period of simple pendulum inside a stationary lift and find T. If lift accelerates upwards with g/3, then time period will be
explanation_txt:
\(\cfrac{T^{\prime}}{T}=\sqrt{\cfrac{g}{g^{\prime}}}=\sqrt{\cfrac{g}{g+\cfrac{g}{3}}}=\sqrt{\cfrac{3}{4}}=\cfrac{\sqrt{3}}{2}\)
\(\therefore \mathrm{T}^{\prime}=\cfrac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \mathrm{T}\)
